 mixing bowl then without measuring cup, cook <b>7-8 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, until caramel is golden brown and glossy. Transfer to a bowl and leave to cool. Clean mixing bowl and continue with recipe."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"Place pecans in mixing bowl and chop <b>1 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a bowl."},{"content":"Place brown sugar, caster sugar, 70 g reserved chopped pecans, cinnamon and salt in mixing bowl then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Spread reserved caramel sauce over the bottom and up the sides of a 32 cm x 20 cm x 5 cm baking dish, then sprinkle over remaining reserved chopped pecans. Place in fridge to chill. Meanwhile, assemble buns."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"On a floured work surface, roll risen dough out into a rectangle (approx. 45 cm x 30 cm). Brush all over with melted butter then sprinkle over reserved sugar and pecan filling."},{"content":"Starting on one long side, roll dough into a tight log. Using a sharp serrated knife, gently cut into 12 pieces, each 4-5 cm wide. Arrange buns cut side up in baking dish over pecan-caramel base, with larger buns around the outside to ensure even cooking."},{"content":"Cover baking dish with cling film and place in fridge overnight (up to 16 hours) until buns have risen and are pressed tightly together in baking dish (see tip)."},{"content":"The next day, remove buns from fridge 1 hour before baking and preheat oven to 180°C."},{"content":"Place baking dish on a large baking tray, then bake for 15 minutes (180°C). Cover with foil and bake for a further 25-30 minutes (180°C) until buns are puffed and golden and internal temperature reads 75°C."},{"content":"Let buns rest in baking dish for 5 minutes, then carefully and quickly invert onto a large serving plate, transferring any caramel left behind to the tops and sides of the buns. Serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If you would prefer to bake the buns the same d